# What is the potential impact of the deputies' actions on the Russia-Ukraine crisis?

## Summary
Deputies from 18 municipal districts in Moscow, St. Petersburg and Kolpino <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font> have called for Russian President Vladimir Putin's resignation <font color=#FF3399>[2, 4, 5]</font> due to his decision to commence a military operation in Ukraine <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. This motion has been supported by most of the districts' deputies <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font> and has been met with criticism on state TV <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. According to the deputies, the military operations goal to de-militarise Ukraine has had the opposite effect <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>, providing Ukraine with modern military equipment and finances worth more than USD 38 billion <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>. The motion has been seen as an attempt to hold Putin accountable and protect the security of Russia and its citizens <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>.

